subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen.
Dorsum of S1 with basal black spot; of S2–5 with a black mid-dorsal stripe beginning at proximal part and extending almost to distal end and terminating in an angulated expansion, S6 with a broad black mid-dorsal stripe, S7 with a black spot at first 1/6 and with a rectangular expansion at distal end, S8–10 dark brown to black. Sides of S1 blue, S2–7 dorso-laterally blue and ventrally pale each with a black apical annulus expanded basally at varying degrees (
Fig. 1a
), S8–10 dark brown to black. Sternum of S1 pale, S3–7 pale with a very narrow black medial stripe, S8 dark brown with a bluish white round spot (
Fig. 6c
). Cercus and genital ligula as described for genus.
